    <measure>Health-Related Quality of Life (HRQoL)</measure>
    <time_frame>3 months</time_frame>
    <description>HRQoL as assessed by the Minnesota Living With Heart Failure Questionnaire (MLHFQ)&#xD;
The MLHFQ is a self-administered questionnaire for patients with HF, comprising 21 items rated on six-point Likert scales, representing different degrees of impact of HF on HRQoL, from 0 (none) to 5 (very much). It provides a total score range 0-105. Lower scores indicate better health-related quality of life (HRQoL).</description>
